------------------------>=2000 (error)
1000 byte of data, sequence


------------------------>=3000
1000 byte of data, sequence

<------------------------ = 2000
No data , Ack 

------------------------>=2000 
1000 byte of data, sequence

<------------------------ = 4000
No data , Ack 








Flow Control 

TCP handles the Flow control through the process called windowing. the two end devices negotiate the window size when initially establishing the connection;
and then renegotiate the window size during the life of connection, increasing the size until it reaches the maximum windows size of 65,535 or until error occure.


